当$AB = BA$, 有

$$(A+B)^n = \sum_{i=0}^n C_n^i A^iB^{n-i} = \sum_{i=0}^n C_n^i B^iA^{n-i}$$

$$
\begin{align*}
e^A e^B &amp;= (\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{A^k}{k!})(\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{B^k}{k!}) \\
&amp;= \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \sum_{i = 0}^{k}\frac{A^i}{i!}\frac{B^{k-i}}{(k-i)!} \\
&amp;= \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \sum_{i = 0}^{k} C_k^i A^i B^{k-i} \frac{1}{k!} \\
&amp;= \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{(A+B)^k}{k!} \\
&amp;= e^{A+B}
\end{align*}
$$

同理

$$e^B e^A = e^{A+B}$$

故

$$e^{A+B}= e^A e^B = e^B e^A$$"><h3>1</h3><p>当<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="9.845ex" height="1.805ex" role="img" focusable="false" viewBox="0 -716 4351.6 798" 因为$|A| \neq 0 $

设$y = x + A^{-1}b$

则

$$\frac{d y}{d t} = A y$$

解: $y = e^{A t} c$

故

$$
\begin{align*}
x &amp;= e^{A t} c - A^{-1}b \\
&amp;= c_1 e^{\frac{-3 + i\sqrt 7}{2} t} \begin{pmatrix}\frac{-1 - i \sqrt 7}{4} \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} + c_2 e^{\frac{-3 - i\sqrt 7}{2} t} \begin{pmatrix}\frac{-1 + i \sqrt 7}{4} \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix}
 -\frac{9}{4} \\
 \frac{11}{4} \\
\end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}
$$

由于$x \in \mathbb{R}^n$

$$
x = e^{-\frac{3}{2}t} \left(c_1 \begin{pmatrix}\frac{- \cos \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t + \sqrt 7 \sin \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t}{4} \\ \cos \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t \end{pmatrix} + c_2 \begin{pmatrix}-\frac{\sqrt 7 \cos \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t + \sin \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t}{4} \\ \sin \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t \end{pmatrix} \right) + \begin{pmatrix}
 \frac{9}{4} \\
 -\frac{11}{4} \\
\end{pmatrix}
$$

div.data-content:
### 1

当$AB = BA$, 有

$$(A+B)^n = \sum_{i=0}^n C_n^i A^iB^{n-i} = \sum_{i=0}^n C_n^i B^iA^{n-i}$$

$$
\begin{align*}
e^A e^B &= (\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{A^k}{k!})(\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{B^k}{k!}) \\
&= \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \sum_{i = 0}^{k}\frac{A^i}{i!}\frac{B^{k-i}}{(k-i)!} \\
&= \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \sum_{i = 0}^{k} C_k^i A^i B^{k-i} \frac{1}{k!} \\
&= \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{(A+B)^k}{k!} \\
&= e^{A+B}
\end{align*}
$$

同理

$$e^B e^A = e^{A+B}$$

故

$$e^{A+B}= e^A e^B = e^B e^A$$

div.data-content:
### 2

因为$|A| \neq 0 $

设$y = x + A^{-1}b$

则

$$\frac{d y}{d t} = A y$$

解: $y = e^{A t} c$

故

$$
\begin{align*}
x &= e^{A t} c - A^{-1}b \\
&= c_1 e^{\frac{-3 + i\sqrt 7}{2} t} \begin{pmatrix}\frac{-1 - i \sqrt 7}{4} \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} + c_2 e^{\frac{-3 - i\sqrt 7}{2} t} \begin{pmatrix}\frac{-1 + i \sqrt 7}{4} \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix}
-\frac{9}{4} \\
\frac{11}{4} \\
\end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}
$$

由于$x \in \mathbb{R}^n$

$$
x = e^{-\frac{3}{2}t} \left(c_1 \begin{pmatrix}\frac{- \cos \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t + \sqrt 7 \sin \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t}{4} \\ \cos \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t \end{pmatrix} + c_2 \begin{pmatrix}-\frac{\sqrt 7 \cos \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t + \sin \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t}{4} \\ \sin \frac{\sqrt 7}{2} t \end{pmatrix} \right) + \begin{pmatrix}
\frac{9}{4} \\
-\frac{11}{4} \\
\end{pmatrix}
$$

div.data-content:
$$|A - \lambda I | = 0$$

$$\Rightarrow \lambda^2 + 3 \lambda+ 4 = 0$$

解得特征值

$$\lambda_1 = \frac{-3 + i\sqrt 7}{2}, \lambda_2 = \frac{-3 - i\sqrt 7}{2}$$

解得:

$\lambda_1$的特征向量 $\begin{pmatrix}\frac{-1 - i \sqrt 7}{4} \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$


$\lambda_2$的特征向量 $\begin{pmatrix}\frac{-1 + i \sqrt 7}{4} \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$
